Thirty-five senior detectives have been moved in changes made by Director of Criminal Investigations Ndegwa Muhoro. On Tuesday, he directed the officers to report to their new stations by April 12. The changes were occasioned by promotions in the directorate. Those promoted and who will head investigations in the counties include; Festus Malinge (Trans Nzoia), Raphael Wawire (Isiolo) and William Ngugi (Garissa). Others posted to police divisions as heads of investigations include; Kennedy Limera (Mt Elgon), Felix Kituku (Msambweni), Martin Karongo (Athi River), Daniel Muleli (Gigiri), Michael Njeru (Tinderet) and Peter Ogolla (Endebes).  